The paper discusses the measurement of interdisciplinarity in science, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the paper examines the Web of Science journal subject categories, which includes categories such as Information Science & Library Science (cs.IR), Cybernetics (cs.CY), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of bibliometric measures, which is relevant to Digital Libraries (cs.DL) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Overall, these sub-categories are the most likely to be relevant to the paper's content.
